    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <head>No. 249.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Chang Yen
                                    Hoon</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 10,
                                1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday’s date, giving me knowledge of the
                            communications to you from your Government in relation to the coming
                            hither of an envoy from the Government of Corea to the United
                            States.</p>
                <p>Shortly after having been thus advised by your note I received from the
                            envoy of Corea, Mr. Pak Chung Yang, a letter by the hands of his
                            secretary asking an interview with me at this Department for the purpose
                            of making an arrangement for the presentation of his credential letter
                            to the President.</p>
                <p>To this I have replied that I shall expect to receive the Corean minister
                            on Friday next, the 13th instant, at 12 o’clock, noon, and shall
                            thereafter at an early day accompany him to be presented to the
                            President in official audience, in the usual manner.</p>
                <p>Accept sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                                Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
